systemTable.name: systemTable

sysSysID.description: The name of the UC4 system. The value of the 'system' keyword in the .INI file of the server.

sysStartTime.name: sysStartTime
sysStartTime.description: The start time of the 1st server of the UC4 system.

sysDbmsName.name: sysDbmsName

clientTable.name: clientTable
clientTable.description: This table contains a row for each UC4 client of all UC4 systems connected to the UC4 SNMP-subagent.

cliSysID.name: cliSysID
cliSysID.description: The symbolic name of the UC4 system the client is a member of.

cliClient.name: cliClient
cliClient.description: The numeric value representation of the client. This number unambiguously identifies the client within a UC4 system.

cliLastModifyTime.name: cliLastModifyTime
cliLastModifyTime.description: Timestamp of the last update of this record.

cliState.name: cliState
cliState.description: The state of UC4 client. Shows whether the execution for this client is permitted (run) or suspended (stop). If a client is in stop state every automatic processing is suspended, but manual intervention is permitted.

cliMonitoring.name: cliMonitoring
cliMonitoring.description: Shows whether the client is important enough his activity to be monitored (productivity client). If yes (1) then the monitoring of the actvity of this client is desired. Monitoring of activity means watching for call operators and blocked jobs.

serverInstanceTable.name: serverInstanceTable
serverInstanceTable.description: This table contains a row for each UC4 Server connected to the UC4 SNMP-subagent.

srvSysID.name: srvSysID
srvSysID.description: The name of the UC4 system the server belongs to. The value of the 'system' keyword in the .INI file of the server.

srvName.name: srvName
srvName.description: The name of the UC4 server. The value of the 'name' keyword in the .INI file of the server.

srvLastModifyTime.name: srvLastModifyTime
srvLastModifyTime.description: Timestamp of the last update of this record.

srvVersion.name: srvVersion
srvVersion.description: The version of the UC4 server.

srvStartTime.name: srvStartTime
srvStartTime.description: Timestamp of the start time of the server.

srvState.name: srvState
srvState.description: The state of the UC4 server. undef(4) a should not be case. run(1) means the server is running. ended(2) means the server ended normaly. abnormal(3) means the server ended abnormaly, or the connection between the server and the UC4 SNMP-subagent has been lost.

srvDiaConnect.name: srvDiaConnect
srvDiaConnect.description: Number of currently connected dialogue clients.

srvBusyMin.name: srvBusyMin
srvBusyMin.description: Statistical Value. Average load of the server in % in the last minute before update.

srvBusy10Min.name: srvBusy10Min
srvBusy10Min.description: Statistical Value. Average load of the server in % in the last 10 minutes before update.

srvBusyHour.name: srvBusyHour
srvBusyHour.description: Statistical Value. Average load of the server in % in the last hour before update.

srvRunMode.name: srvRunMode
srvRunMode.description: The role of the server in the UC4 system. undef(3) yet unset primary(1) the server is a primary in the UC4 system. standby(2) the server is a standby in the UC4 system.

srvDBState.name: srvDBState
srvDBState.description: The status of the connection between the UC4 server and the UC4 database. undef(3) online(1) offline(2)

srvSDBState.name: srvSDBState
srvSDBState.description: The status of the connection between the UC4 server and the UC4 status database. 4 = noSDB no SRRC (Status Recording Recovery and Control), 1 = online SDB is online, status recording works 2 = offline because of failure(s) SDB has been switched off 3 = dismounted SDB is unaccessable

executorTable.name: executorTable
executorTable.description: This table contains a row for each UC4 executor connected to any server that is connected to the UC4 SNMP-subagent.

exeSysID.name: exeSysID
exeSysID.description: The name of the UC4 system the executor belongs to. The value of the 'system' keyword in the .INI file of the server.

exeSrvName.name: exeSrvName
exeSrvName.description: The name of the server the executor is connected to.

exeName.name: exeName
exeName.description: The name of the executor. The value of the 'name' keyword in the .INI file of the executor.

exeType.name: exeType
exeType.description: The type of the executor. The value of the 'typ' keyword in the .INI file of the executor.

exeLastModifyTime.name: exeLastModifyTime
exeLastModifyTime.description: Timestamp of the last update of this record.

exeHost.name: exeHost
exeHost.description: The name of the executor's host. The value of the 'host' keyword in the .INI file of the executor

exeHardware.name: exeHardware
exeHardware.description: CPU type obtained by the executor from the run-time environment.

exeSoftware.name: exeSoftware
exeSoftware.description: The executor is running for software.

exeSoftwareVers.name: exeSoftwareVers
exeSoftwareVers.description: OS type obtained by the executor from the run-time environment.

exeJCLTyp.name: exeJCLTyp
exeJCLTyp.description: Job Control Language for job generation. The value of the 'UC_HOST_JCL_VAR' keyword in the .INI file of the executor

exeConnTime.name: exeConnTime
exeConnTime.description: Timestamp of the last connection setup of the executor.

exeState.name: exeState
exeState.description: The state of the executor. undef(5) not set yet run(1) the executor is working ended(2) the executor is stopped or not started yet lost(3) the connection between the executor and the server has been broken. timeout(4) the connection on the transport layer seems to be OK, but the application (executor) does not respond

exeLastPing.name: exeLastPing
exeLastPing.description: The timestamp of the last attempt to get life-sign from the executor..

exeMonitoring.name: exeMonitoring
exeMonitoring.description: Shows whether the executor is important enough its availability to be monitored (productivity executor). If yes (1) then the monitoring of the availability of this executor is desired.

blkObjRunNr.description: The run number of the object that caused the blocking.
